The South African Football Association seemingly never-ending financial woes have seen them flagged offside once again and facing the attachment of their assets. Safa advocate McCaps Motimele has applied for judgment in the Johannesburg High Court against the football body for its failure to pay him more than R600,000 for legal services. Motimele filed the summons on Monday giving Safa 10 days to file notice to oppose his claim with failure to do so possibly resulting in judgment granted against them. If the judgment is granted, Motimele may also be granted a writ of execution to attach and auction off Safa's assets to recoup his moolah. GET A COPY OF THE SUNDAY WORLD FOR THE FULL STORY